climbs.name: Shark Tooth
climbs.fa: Ian CB and Ben Strobel probably.

content.description: From an obvious sit, left hand on the arete and right on a slanting, glassy sidepull, climb the arete trending slightly right to finish.  A sustained and very good problem.
content.protection: Pads and spotter, maybe 4 pads minimum but more would be better.
content.location: 100 yards west of the Ejaculator Boulder.  A 10 minute walk east from the Reserve, the Boulder is just below the rim of the south bluff (towards the lake) and visible.  A prominent pillar feature is 40 feet west of the Boulder.

content.description: Path of least resistance on the the boulder. Start on the right arete with a right hand tooth, left hand edge. work your way up to easy moves on the slab.
content.location: To the right of the Secrets of the Lake project.

content.description: Start on a low edge/undercling and go up the face trending right.  Couple of obvious crimps on the face.
Start with right hand on jug underneath the roof and left hand on slopey edge. A few powerful moves lead up the arete.

Start on the overhanging west face of the Shark Tooth Boulder, left hand down on a slanting, glassy rail (starting right hand for Shark Tooth) and right just above on a glassy crimp.  Get a toehook out right, establish on the wall and float your way to the top.  A strange problem that might just suck you in!
Start on two good pods in opposing cracks low in the dihedral.  Climb out crimps on the left wall to an exposed but easy top out.
content.protection: This one is kind of hard to pad, so probably best to not fall off.
content.location: The obvious dihedral next to the Sharks Tooth.

content.description: Just a 100 yards west of The Ejaculator Boulder is a few sweet blocks. Check out the pics. Not sure what has been done.
